sn35.219-221:0.3: 219–221. The Exterior and What’s Not-Self in the Three Times
sn35.219-221:1.1: “Mendicants, in the past … future … present sights, sounds, smells, tastes, touches, and thoughts are not-self.
sn35.219-221:1.2: And what’s not-self should be truly seen with right understanding like this: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’ …”
